[{"question":"There\u0027s no political tea leaves to be read here?","answer":"We don\u0027t have any tea.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":27,"aSentId":28},{"question":"What was your assessment?","answer":"Well, I think that she engaged.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":117,"aSentId":118},{"question":"And is there any doubt that she\u0027ll run in 2016?","answer":"I think there -- I think there\u0027s a doubt.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":136,"aSentId":137},{"question":"And I suppose the key question is, what do you collectively think can actually be achieved here?","answer":"Well, I thought it was an excellent meeting, and it went beyond just the narrow topic of assault weapons into the broader topic of gun violence in general.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":165,"aSentId":166},{"question":"Or is it true that the majority of American people don\u0027t really want one?","answer":"Well, from my personal perspective and what we dealt with in some of the things I have seen over 28 years in law enforcement, I personally don\u0027t think banning any weapon is going to stop the problem.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":183,"aSentId":184},{"question":"Do you?","answer":"Well, the problem that I see that we\u0027re missing here is we have a situation that because we\u0027re talking about gun violence at the forefront, we\u0027re missing the issue that I think is really paramount throughout all of America.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":203,"aSentId":204},{"question":"Explain to me how you think the best way of dealing with the handgun issue could be going forward?","answer":"When you say the best way, obviously, you have to look at things that are possible.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":222,"aSentId":223},{"question":"Do you see any reason why you need to have assault rifles in civilian hands generally?","answer":"I don\u0027t see a reason for it.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":230,"aSentId":231},{"question":"How do you try and deal with that mentality in a reasonable way that doesn\u0027t offend gun owners but actually works to reduce the total volume of guns rather than dramatically increase it?","answer":"ELLY: The Second Amendment is here to stay.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":241,"aSentId":242},{"question":"Can any of these laws -- from a law enforcement perspective, can any of them be properly effective if they are not federal laws?","answer":"Ninety percent of the guns that we confiscate here on the streets of New York City are coming from out of state.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":250,"aSentId":251},{"question":"Is it time for more politicians to show a bit of backbone and a bit of personal courage over this rather than worrying about their political futures?","answer":"Yes, I don\u0027t think it\u0027s too much to ask for our elected officials to vote your conscience.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":261,"aSentId":262},{"question":"How do we get this debate to the correct place where real action can be done that will have real effects on curbing gun violence?","answer":"Well, that\u0027s exactly the 64,000 dollar question.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":306,"aSentId":307},{"question":"Really?","answer":"I don\u0027t accept that you have to start some place.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":336,"aSentId":337},{"question":"Isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, that\u0027s supposing that their conscious tells them that\u0027s the right thing to do.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":349,"aSentId":350},{"question":"But do you agree that the answer to gun violence is categorically not to reduce the volume of guns in circulation?","answer":"Yes, I do agree.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":363,"aSentId":364},{"question":"And yet you\u0027re aware that obviously every country that has brought in tough gun control, almost without exception, around the world, from Japan to Australia to Britain, has seen dramatic reductions in the amount of gun murders and gun-related crimes?","answer":"Right, but if you look at -- the United States isn\u0027t even in the top ten of leaders in the category of violent crimes, Piers.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":368,"aSentId":369},{"question":"Presumably -- I mean, do you agree or disagree with the ban on machine guns, for example, automatic machine guns?","answer":"Well, that\u0027s a reasonable restriction.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":400,"aSentId":401},{"question":"And that\u0027s why I don\u0027t understand why you\u0027re comfortable with banning one and not the other?","answer":"It\u0027s not a question of what I\u0027m comfortable with.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":407,"aSentId":408},{"question":"What is the difference?","answer":"The AR-15 is semiautomatic, Piers.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":432,"aSentId":433},{"question":"Dana, other -- Dana, other than keeping guns in people\u0027s hand -- I have your point on that -- what would you proactively do to reduce gun violence?","answer":"Tougher penalties for criminals who kill people with illegally obtained fire arms.","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":493,"aSentId":494},{"question":"Did that answer your question?","answer":"Charles --","docId":"130128pmt","qSentId":496,"aSentId":497}]